/* MEMORY PRINTER: MATCH WITH FIRST BYTE 255 */
>+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.-------------------.--.++++++++++++++++++.-.-----------.++++++.-.------------------------------------------------------------------------------.+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.++++++++++++.--.+++.----.-------.+++++++++++++++.---------------.-------------------------------------------------------. // Print message
>++++++++++. // Print newline
>+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.---..-------------.+++++++++.++++++.------------------------------------------------------------------------------------.+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++.--------.++++++++.++.+++.+++++++.---------------------------------------------------------------. // Print another message
<.> // Print newline; go to edge

>- // Set right memory edge at edge (byte 255)
<+ // Add 1 (setup)
[ // Go to left memory edge (first byte labeled 255)
    -<+
]
- // Undo last addition
[ // Print until right memory edge
    ->.+
]
> // Go to next empty byte
